This repository ships an A-to-Z agentic development skill set. Its behavior
contract lives in [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) at the repo root — read it first.

**The gate (from `meta/using-skills`):** if there is even a 1% chance a skill in
`skills/**/SKILL.md` applies to what you are about to do, invoke that skill
first — before clarifying questions, before exploring the codebase, before
editing a file. Announce "Using [skill] to [purpose]", then follow the skill
body exactly.

**The four Iron Laws are hard prohibitions, not guidelines:**

- **NO-CODE** — `brainstorm` and a stated ceremony tier before any spec work.
- **TEST-FIRST** — no production code without a failing test first (`tdd`).
- **ROOT-CAUSE** — no fix without root-cause investigation (`debug`).
- **EVIDENCE** — no completion claim without fresh verification (`verify`).

Cursor has no session-start hook, so this rule is the injection path that keeps
the gate alive. The full skill inventory, trace-spine contract, and subagent
protocol are in AGENTS.md.
